For upgrading [`serde_with 2.0.0`](https://crates.io/crates/serde_with)
`map_as_tuple_list` can be replaced with `#[serde_as(as = "Vec<(_, _)>")]` as described in this [page](https://github.com/jonasbb/serde_with/releases).

``` Rust
use serde_derive::{Deserialize, Serialize};
use std::collections::HashMap;
use ::serde_with::serde_as;

#[serde_as(crate = "::serde_with")]
#[derive(Debug, Default, Serialize, Deserialize, Clone)]
pub struct TestStruct {
    // #[serde(with = "serde_with::rust::map_as_tuple_list")]
    #[serde_as(as = "Vec<(_, _)>")]
    pub hashmap: HashMap<String, String>,
}

fn main() {
    let cfg = TestStruct {
        hashmap: HashMap::from([
            ("1".to_owned(), "1".to_owned()),
            ("2".to_owned(), "2".to_owned()),
        ]),
        ..Default::default()
    };
    let res = toml::to_string_pretty(&cfg);
    println!("{}", &res.as_ref().unwrap());

    let cfg2 = toml::from_str::<TestStruct>(&res.unwrap());
    println!("{:?}", &cfg2);
}
```

Or drop  [`serde_with`](https://crates.io/crates/serde_with), by moving all fields with HashMap to the end of the struct.

