Previously we use line mode, but sciter emit a lot of events at one scrolling(fling), so the scroll speed will be too fast.

Sciter set direction into x,y (-1, 0, 1), and power into buttons. But the values of buttons vary, they didn't  this on documentations, so it will be unreliable. 

here is a code snippet I try to use event, it didn't work so will. 

```rust
#[inline]
#[cfg(target_os = "macos")]
fn fix_scroll_in_mac(mut x: i32, mut y: i32, buttons: i32) -> (i32, i32) {
    // mac can only have one direction.
    // Weird buttons value, it can be different signal with x,y
    use std::cmp::{max, min};
    let new_y = if y == -1 {
        y * (-buttons + 0xfffe) / 0xffff
    } else if y == 1 {
        y * buttons
    } else {
        y
    };

    let new_x = if x == 1 {
        x * (buttons + 0x1ffff) / 0x20000
    } else if x == -1 {
        x * (-buttons + 0x1ffff) / 0x20000
    } else {
        x
    };
    log::info!("old xy {x} {y}, new xy {new_x} {new_y} btn {buttons}");
    (x * 3, y * 3)
}

``` 

* 3 means to speed up the scrolling, and I tested in my mac(m1 and x86), it works.
